<TITLE> LDP wants JS polls first </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 8 (bdnews24.com)The Liberal Democratic Party pressed for holding polls to Jatiya Sangsad before any other at its electoral dialogue with the Election Commission on Monday. LDP will in no case accept Upazila elections before national polls, president Oli Ahmed told reporters after attending the dialogue. However, he added: "The schedules for both elections may be announced together." "The Upazila polls may be held two weeks after the parliamentary elections," he added. LDP also pressed the government to lift the emergency immediately and allow indoor politics across the country, said Oli who led his party's delegation that included Redwan Ahmed, Alamgir Kabir and Jahanara Begum. The EC is scheduled to meet another four political parties, including the Awami League, on Tuesday. The AL has notified the EC of its plan of attending its dialogue session with an eight-strong team. Jatiya Party (JP-Manju) The Election Commission also sat with Jatiya Party (JP-Manju) Monday from 12:30-1:30pm. Exiting from the EC conference room, JP secretary general Sheikh Shahidul Islam told reporters that they had pressed the government to lift the emergency immediately. JP had endorsed the idea of announcing schedules for parliamentary elections, upazila polls and the Dhaka City Corporation election simultaneously, Islam said. He also said that the EC might consult major political parties before taking a decision in this regard. JP delegates included Sadeque Siddiqui, Abdur Rahim, Mrs Amena Bari and Mofizul Haq Bebu. bdnews2
